metadata.name: Draad #113
metadata.description:
[…]

At some point, the Artificial Intelligence hooked itself up to a mechanical looming machine.

Being its only way of manifesting itself in the physical world, the AI began communicating through it.

The rigid patterns of horizontal and vertical threads turned out to be insufficient for what the AI had to say. And through the network, it branched out. It found a way of manipulating individual threads by attaching itself to a chenille embroidery machine. This seemingly openened up a whole new vocabulary.

Many have tried to communicate back or propose other ways of communicating by attaching multiple digital devices to the network.

It seems to be only interested in threads.

[…]

–

Draad ("thread", in Dutch) is a responsive generative artwork. Its canonical form is 1:1, but it scales to 2:3 or 3:2 depending on the viewport.

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[?scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[?width=<number>&height=<number>] set the dimensions.
[?animation=false] skip animating the threads.
[?mode=duotone] activate duotone mode.
[?mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in duotone mode: SVG file in two colors, suitable for plotting with two pens.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file in black, suitable for plotting with a single pen.

© 2022 Monokai.

metadata.name: Colin #4
metadata.description:
Finally, the avatar project you've all been waiting for. Profile pictures that truly reflect our unique personalities. A chance to show how individual we are.

With a wide range of clothes and hairstyles, expressions ranging from 'Existential Dread' to 'Overwhelming Anxiety', and exciting colours from 'Brilliant Beige' to 'Wonderful Wheat', it's time to bring some sparkle to Web3.


*Please note, all Colin's will almost certainly look the same*


Contact @iamnotwal if you'd like to be added to the Beige-List!


(Layered compositions made possible because of @PureSpider's generously shared template.)

metadata.name: Conspiracy Theory #127
metadata.description:
The idea is inspired by the conspiracy board.

Conspiracy theories may go so far that even people, in newspapers and books, look for clues. 
The text is from Alice in Wonderland, which is randomly selected and then words are selected to be highlighted and circled, and eventually numbers may be written next to some of them to create a network of clues.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.
Made with P5js.

metadata.name: WTBS Logo with Friends #258
metadata.description:
Did you know that WTBS is now sixth months old? If we were Will’s baby, we’d be sitting up and prepping to crawl — the literal baby steps that precede an entire lifetime of movement. 

Play is another integral part of our development. Play teaches us to connect, laugh, share, love, and learn. It helps form our earliest friendships that mold us into who we are destined to become. Over the last six months we have had the immense pleasure of forming new relationships with some of the amazing artists that comprise of the fxhash community. 

It is the love and support of new friends Laurent Houdard, Ada Ada Ada, elsif, and Camille Roux that made our first (official) collaboration possible. Thank you so much for the idea, the vision, the art, the time, and the wrangling to make this possible. 

Each letter is imbued with the unique style of an artist, based on a framework created by Laurent. There is a small chance of receiving a piece with two of the same style, with the rarest possibility of receiving one with all four quadrants the same. 

Collect with love and the knowledge that your support means the world to us. Thank you for listening every week, and for the messages and stories that you share with us. We can’t wait to continue to grow.

Thank you so much again to Laurent, Ada, elsif, and Camille. This is what community is.

metadata.name: Lines of Solitude #45
metadata.description:
There is a mystery in the lifeline, where we walk and discover all alone. Some landscapes make we breath this solitude.

- 17 palettes available.
- 2 Styles of landscapes (Desert and Sea).
- 2 Colors of Sea (Red and Blue).
- The Desert may contain cactus.

Press the [S] key in live view to save a "Lines of solitude".jpg file.

This artwork was created with p5.js

Collab: Nobody (@jorgemauro1000) and Ad Mortem Festinamus (@AFestinamus).

metadata.name: Sirkel #45
metadata.description:
Sirkel is an exploration on circular shapes, grid and bold lines.
While the artwork is heavily dependant on the grid, the neighbouring elements can line up seamlessly. It’s a slight nod to op art mixed with minimalistic grid based designs.

- 3 different line weights
- 3 grid sizes
- 3 block styles
- 3 palettes + occasional dark version

Press “s” to save a 4096x4096px image.

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #231
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Lands of Solitude #125
metadata.description:
In times of chaos and uncertainty while the digital world falls appart, some will decide to resist and build. In their blind quest for curiosity, knowledge and creation, they will endure the darkest times and as waves of departures will follow one another, very few will remain. These are the lands of solitude that await.

Controls :
* Drag and pan to rotate and zoom.
* Press « F » to toggle the All-Over mode.
* Press « G » to toggle the grid.
* Press « H » to toggle the in-world infos.
* Press the space bar to toggle the auto scroll mode.
* Press « R » to restart.

———————

Lands of Solitude by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Elevation #124
metadata.description:
There’s so much more to our world than what we are able to perceive, let alone understand. Will we ever be able to even fully understand ourselves?

–

Elevation is a series of 320 generative elevation drawings of imaginary structures. It is a reminder of the limits of our consciousness, and an ode to the manifold nuances that lie beyond what we can perceive, beyond what we even can imagine.

As a generative artist, I aim to elevate my own consciousness with the help of the machine. I welcome algorithms and randomness into the creation of my works, taking full control, and intentionally giving it away, always seeking to expand my imagination. For as humans alone, we remain limited to our own edifice of thought, and often fail to free ourselves from the visible, mundane world.

Both are present in Elevation: the visible and the imaginary, the mundane and the transcendent, the solid and the fragile. Where an architect’s elevation drawing marks the transition from the thought world into the visible world, Elevation remains in-between, depicting both the idea of an imaginary structure, and the structure itself.

–

Elevation is intended for print. All holders of an Elevation NFT will be able to order the corresponding signed print in the respective paper format via andreasrau.eu/elevation. Press [s] to save the image as displayed or [p] to generate a print-ready PNG image at 300 dpi. This might take a while, depending on paper format and your hardware.

–

Elevation
p5.js, glsl, html, css
Andreas Rau, 2022

metadata.name: Balancium #138
metadata.description:
"Balancium" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

In the fall of 1931, in Alexander Calder's studio, Marcel Duchamp coined the term 'mobile' for his kinetic sculptures. Later, Calder wrote: "This, in French, means not only 'movable'— but also a 'motive', 'a reason for an act' so I found it a very good word."
 
Around the same year, Bruno Munari started making colorful and whimsical mobiles. He called them "useless machines", existing without any purpose and inviting viewers to just look. Elements are connected with nearly invisible threads or wires, allowing the artist to create the illusion of shapes floating in the air.

Balancium is both a virtual mobile and a useless object. Generated by the code, it undergoes a continual transformation. The movement of the air, or invisible fluid, becomes an integral part of the design and amplifies serenity. 
 
There is a keyboard key that unlocks more variations.
